{"title":"CeramicSpeed’s new OSPW X derailleur cage matches your fork – Sea Otter Classic 2023 randoms","link":"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/04/ceramicspeed-ospw-x-sea-otter-classic-2023/","date":1682186767000,"content":"<figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/CeramicSpeed-OSPW-X-cage-two.jpg?width=1200\" alt=\"CeramicSpeed's new OSPW X derailleur cage matches your fork – Sea Otter Classic 2023 randoms\" /></figure><p><span>Think of your favorite day of the year, add bikes, tons of racing, and one of the most beautiful backdrops you can think of, and you have the <a href=\"http://cyclingtips.com/tag/Sea-Otter-Classic\" target=\"_blank\">Sea Otter Classic</a> 2023. This is perhaps the single biggest bicycle gear and accessory show in North America, with over 1,000 vendors and 300 individual races to see here. </span></p>\n<p><span>Day two of our favorite gear and accessories from the Sea Otter Classic is here. Some of our favorites include an ultralight and padded saddle from Wove Bike, some new bikes from Vitus, and a matchy-match <a href=\"http://cyclingtips.com/tag/CeramicSpeed\" target=\"_blank\">CeramicSpeed</a> pulley and cage system.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Also read: </strong><a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/04/decathlon-bikes-titanium-gravel/\" target=\"_blank\">Decathlon is bringing a $3999 titanium gravel bike to the U.S. – Sea Otter Classic 2023</a></p>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Wove-Mags-bike-saddle-side.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Wove-Mags-bike-saddle-side\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Wove-Mags-bike-saddle-side.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Wove-Mags-bike-saddle-side.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>Wove Bike has released a new saddle at Sea Otter Classic called the Wove Mags. Here’s the lowdown: The Mags is a short-nose saddle that weighs just 126 grams, but is more padded than just about any performance-oriented saddle I’ve ever seen. Perhaps only the Specialized Mirror saddles come close. (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</figcaption></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Wove-Mags-bike-saddle-rails.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Wove-Mags-bike-saddle-rails\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Wove-Mags-bike-saddle-rails.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Wove-Mags-bike-saddle-rails.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>The saddle comes in at 240 mm long. The unidirectional round carbon rails are said to be extremely strong, with seatpost bolts breaking before the rails do. (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Wove-Mags-bike-saddle-base.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Wove-Mags-bike-saddle-base\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Wove-Mags-bike-saddle-base.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Wove-Mags-bike-saddle-base.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>Wove says that there is no weight limit for their high-end saddles, surprising against the likes of an Ergon SR Allroad Core Pro saddle or others that have a weight limit. (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>Vitus has a range of cool bikes recently released. This is the Venon Evo, which is a fast gravel and allroad bike that they think the majority of drop bar cyclists really want. Here’s the bike set up with a 2x drivetrain and 28 mm tires… (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</figcaption></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-full.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-full\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-full.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-full.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>And the same Venon Evo frame in a different build kit, including a 1x drivetrain and 40mm knobby gravel tires. The bike comes with fender mounts, but no bottom bracket bottle cage one might expect from a gravel bike. (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</figcaption></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-seatstays.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-seatstays\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-seatstays.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-seatstays.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>Stay tuned as we have a Vitus Venon Evo in for review soon. Like Vitus, we think this might just be the bike that most drop bar bike riders are looking for. (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</figcaption></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-turquoise.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-turquoise\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-turquoise.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-turquoise.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>The turquoise colorway carries through the VItus 2023 lineup. (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</figcaption></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-ZX-1-austin-aviators-bike.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Vitus-ZX-1-austin-aviators-bike\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-ZX-1-austin-aviators-bike.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-ZX-1-austin-aviators-bike.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>NCL fans will be happy to see the Vitus ZX-1 EVO road bike here in the Austin Aviators livery. This one is inspired by aviation with the AA-23 logos and colors. (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</figcaption></figure>\n<figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-ZX-1-Austin-Aviators-bike-512.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Vitus-ZX-1-Austin-Aviators-bike-512\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-ZX-1-Austin-Aviators-bike-512.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-ZX-1-Austin-Aviators-bike-512.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>512 fans stand up! Real Austin heads (and folks with Austin area codes) know what’s up. (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/CeramicSpeed-OSPW-X-cage-turquoise.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"CeramicSpeed-OSPW-X-cage-turquoise\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/CeramicSpeed-OSPW-X-cage-turquoise.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/CeramicSpeed-OSPW-X-cage-turquoise.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>CeramicSpeed has brought a range of their OSPW X off-road low-friction cages to Sea Otter Classic. Shown here are some limited-edition cages in two limited-edition Cerakote finishes. Here’s one in “Icy Blue.” (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</figcaption></figure>\n<div></div>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/CeramicSpeed-OSPW-X-cage-two.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"CeramicSpeed-OSPW-X-cage-two\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" /><figcaption>Fans of the color orange (I know you’re out there) will be happy to find a “Fiery Orange” Cerakote finish of the CeramicSpeed OSPW X. This is paired with a gold finish for the pulleys. (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)<img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/CeramicSpeed-OSPW-X-cage-Fiery-Orange-bike.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"CeramicSpeed-OSPW-X-cage-Fiery-Orange-bike\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/CeramicSpeed-OSPW-X-cage-Fiery-Orange-bike.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/CeramicSpeed-OSPW-X-cage-Fiery-Orange-bike.jpg?width=190 190w\" /></figcaption></figure>\n<p><span>Huh, it looks not dissimilar to the Fox Factory fork in orange with Kashima coat. Curious. (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</span></p>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Ventum-ES1-G-electric-gravel-bike.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Ventum-ES1-G-electric-gravel-bike\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Ventum-ES1-G-electric-gravel-bike.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Ventum-ES1-G-electric-gravel-bike.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>Ventum has a new electric gravel bike coming soon called the ES1 G. The Ventum ES1 G is a Class 3 electric bike offering pedal assist up to 28 mph. Additionally, it offers 700c x 50 mm tire clearance, internal cable routing with a standard stem, and Ventum’s aero tube shapes. (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Ventum-ES1-G-electric-gravel-bike-XT-Di2.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Ventum-ES1-G-electric-gravel-bike-XT-Di2\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Ventum-ES1-G-electric-gravel-bike-XT-Di2.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Ventum-ES1-G-electric-gravel-bike-XT-Di2.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption><span>Interestingly, this ES1 G build uses the new Shimano XT Di2 drivetrain (powered by the central battery) and a SRAM UDH derailleur hanger. (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</span></figcaption></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Ventum-ES1-G-electric-gravel-bike-controller.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Ventum-ES1-G-electric-gravel-bike-controller\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Ventum-ES1-G-electric-gravel-bike-controller.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Ventum-ES1-G-electric-gravel-bike-controller.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>The top tube carries an integrated power button and and assist controller. Up top is a small Shimano display to the right of the stem. (Photo: Alvin Holbrook/CyclingTips)</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure></figure>\n<figure></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-Aviators-logo.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-Aviators-logo\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-Aviators-logo.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Vitus-Venon-Evo-gravel-bike-Aviators-logo.jpg?width=190 190w\" /></figure>","author":"Alvin Holbrook","siteTitle":"CyclingTips","siteHash":"30feca30fb3902119bf2da6559e7337232527b61c9abe0a00f5d7543c6aa6c84","entryHash":"b8a6f248f1236faa05fba9637a22a8e029354d1df0a3d01dd8264047afa655e8","category":"Cycling"}